        <dcterms:abstract>&lt;p&gt;Micro-grids are advanced energy systems that leverage digital technologies, data-driven insights, and robust cybersecurity measures to optimize energy management, enhance grid stability, and protect against cyber threats. Micro-grids are decentralized energy systems that can operate independently or in coordination with the main power grid. Their ability to integrate renewable energy sources that optimize energy management makes them a sustainable and resilient solution. The research objectives are to understand the micro-grid community and advance innovate these energy systems. The two most important problems are complexity and cybersecurity. &lt;/p&gt;</dcterms:abstract>
