        <dc:title>Implementation SCADA Web Client For Monitoring Geothermal Power Plant 3 MW Kamojang - Indonesia</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>The development of increasingly advanced internet technology causes every piece of equipment to be connected to the internet. The Supervisory Control And Data Acquisition (SCADA) system integrates control systems with computer equipment (software and hardware) to monitor, collect data, and control equipment from a certain distance using a local network or connected to the internet. Therefore, an innovation has been made in the SCADA system architecture at the Geothermal Power Plant (GPP) 3 MW, namely the addition of the SCADA web to facilitate monitoring and supervision of the GPP 3 MW system. SCADA Web Client will display all monitoring data selected from the SCADA Web Server to be published to the client. Solutions with this system save in terms of time and cost. The principal at the head office, about 250 km from the GPP 3 MW Kamojang, was curious about the real-time operation of the site with the same display on the site's monitor screen. It also aims to be able to provide the right and quick decisions in the event of an alarm or problem in the field. Based on the test results, the data on the web server is the same as that on the SCADA web so that valid data between data sent by the server and data received by the client can be used for analysis, prediction, monitoring, Etc. Design using SCADA IWS v7.1.</dcterms:abstract>
