        <dc:title>Complexity Assessment of Research Space for Smart City Cybersecurity</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>The article aims to draw a space for cybersecurity challenges for smart cities from a systematic perspective. The focus of the research is on a general view grounded in the three-dimensional approach. It exhaustively presents a metaspace needed for research on smart city cybersecurity. The proposed space for research is based on a taxonomy following a systematic review of smart city cybersecurity challenges. It enables assessing the complexity of space from the cybersecurity problems of the smart city.</dcterms:abstract>
