        <dc:title>Evolution of AI in CPS: Enhancing Technical Capabilities and Human Interactions</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>The main goal of this chapter is to discuss how artificial intelligence (AI) is potentially used in cyber-physical systems. Additionally, the focus of the discussion will be on its real-time applications and attributes of human interactions. The focus of the literature review is on identifying the growing influence of AI in e-CPS that supports both technical and human levels. This helps in analyzing data, drawing conclusions, making predictions, and overall making better judgments using a set of tools called artificial intelligence (AI). Consequently, several academic and business articles were reviewed to support the conclusions. Natural sciences and social sciences differ from one another, making it impossible to apply traditional scientific procedures to social sciences. However, this example might be improved with the application of AI and knowledge technology in general in economics. It may evaluate its effect on the real world by simulating human behavior. Making more accurate predictions as well as spotting financial bubbles and other possible economic weaknesses may be made simpler as a result. While its instruments can violate privacy protections, its algorithms have the potential to strengthen already biased practices. Adhering to values like responsibility, transparency, and fairness will help address these flaws.</dcterms:abstract>
