        <dc:title>Harnessing the value of data using the systems thinking approach</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>Water utilities are evolving into complex cyber-physical-human systems as a result of digital transformation. However, there is an absence of clear pathways that can guide water utilities to implement effective data governance practices and realise the value of data. Challenges are emerging around managing changing data characteristics, technology integration and interoperability, leveraging artificial intelligence and machine learning practices, cybersecurity and regulatory compliance. This paper highlights the applicability and benefits of the systems thinking approach for navigating the digital transformation with a focus on data management. Systems thinking mapping and modelling can enable water utilities to maximise the value of data by identifying the interconnections and interdependencies among influencing factors and associated risks and intervention areas. This study used a desktop literature study to demonstrate the applicability of a systems thinking framework for identifying and analysing influencing factors and their complex interrelationships related to data management for harnessing data value. Systems mapping and modelling enable the early identification of risks and strategic intervention points in data management. Future research should explore how the systems thinking approach can be extended to identify actions and pathways for managing technology integration, assessing organisational readiness, implementing effective data governance strategies and facilitating data-driven decision-making.</dcterms:abstract>
